questions.text:
Hey, you. You're finally awake.

Today's your first day at your new job. Don't screw it up!
You have three different modes of transportation. Which do you use to go to work?
You hop onto the ATV, turn the ignition, and head to work. It takes twenty minutes to get to work.
You pull into the parking lot only to find there are no more spaces left, except for a small vehicles only spot near the dumpsters.

answers.text: Park your ATV by the dumpster.
Park your Dodge Charger by the dumpster.

questions.text: Your ATV fits perfectly into the spot.
You approach the door to the building and attempt to open it. It is locked.

answers.text: You see a person walking towards you. Ask them for help.

questions.text: You look around.

answers.text: Look under the mat for a key.
You see a cat hop down from a tree and walk around the corner of the building. Follow the cat.
There is a vending machine next to the door. Buy something from the vending machine.

questions.text: You find a key under the mat. You make a mental note to talk to security later.
You approach a back entrance.
You open the door.
The cat purrs in gratitude.
VIP Meeting Room
Your mind blanks. Unsure what to do, you decide to juggle. You fail utterly, you carrots falling to the ground. You never were a great juggler.

You recall the company's mission statement and values from the pamphlet you read earlier. You give a dramatic, heartfelt speech, to which you receive an outstanding applause. The meeting leader shakes your hand and hands you a VIP card along with some awesome company swag!
On your way to your desk, you meet your coworkers.

answers.text: Offer them some of your swag!

questions.text: You reach your desk at last. You find a sandwich alignment chart and a note reading: "Welcome to the team! It is standard procedure for new employees to answer life's most important question. How do you define a sandwich? Choose wisely."

answers.text: A Chip Butty is a Sandwich.
Ice Cream Between Waffles is a Sandwich
A hot dog is a sandwich
An ice cream taco is a sandwich.
A chicken wrap is a sandwich
A sushi burrito is a sandwich

questions.text: You've chosen to define a sandwich as having two separate pieces of bread.
You're not exactly a sandwich purist, but you're not a radicalist either.

answers.text: The cat you met from earlier suddenly reappears, beckoning you with its tail. Follow the cat.

questions.text: The cat leads you up, down, left, down, right, until you've completely forgotten where you are. At least, you descend some steps to a heavy black door with the words "RSA Only" written on it. You recognize this as the Radical Sandwich Anarchy.

answers.text: Turn around. You've changed your mind!
Ask the cat to open the door.
Ask the cat to open the door.

questions.text: You are indicted into the Radical Sandwich Anarchy and sworn to silence. You have a new mission, and that is to set sandwiches free.
The cat scratches at the door. You hear sounds of movement on the other side before it opens, revealing darkness. On the floor sits a cake.

answers.text: Turn around fast! This is just getting weird.
Obviously, that's not a cake, but a sandwich. You know what you have to do.

questions.text: You send out a message to your coworkers that lunch is on you, and you're having sandwiches. You smile to yourself. This is only the beginning.
The cat just stares at you. Their eyes glitter with what you believe is amusement.

At the end of your training, your boss sends you an email. "Congratulations! You are our very first employee to have received a raise on their first day. Thank you for going above and beyond, and we very much look forward to working with you!"
Congratulations! You've completed your first day of work with relatively few troubles.
Your boss informs you that you are not a good fit for the job.
You've chosen to define a sandwich on your own terms.
You give everyone an ice cream bar. They seem to really like you.
You give everyone a coffee. They seem to like you.
You offer your coworkers your dirty carrots. "Ewwwwww!" They don't actually say, but you can see the disgust plainly on their faces.
You offer them some of your swag. They are amazed and seem to really like you.
You go to your desk.
Your coworkers shake their head.
Your coworkers take the string cheese.

Why did the cranberry sauce turn red?


...


"It saw the turkey dressing!"

The room groans in unison. The VIP leader points to the door.
You stand awkwardly for a few minutes before excusing yourself from the room.
The ice cream bars melt from the exertion.
The string cheeses slip out of your sweaty palms and land on the ground.
There are only four items left. What do you buy?

answers.text: Monster Coffee! You need the energy boost.
Ice Cream Bar! You deserve a treat.
Nothing! Go back to looking around.

questions.text: You buy a coffee.
You buy a cheesestick.
You buy carrots.
It's your lucky day! The vending machine accidentally pushes more than one ice cream bars out.
The lock turns with a satisfying click.
You wait.

The confidence you felt earlier remains. Of course you can fit your Dodge Charger into the very, very small spot. After all, you don't want to be late to work.

You manage to squeeze your Dodge Charger in, but not without knocking off your right side mirror and scraping your back right bumper.

Good thing is, you're fifteen minutes early.
You find a parking spot in the lot two blocks over. It sets you 10 minutes behind schedule.

You decide to take the shuttle. It takes 5 minutes to arrive at your stop, 20 minutes to get there, and 5 minutes to get to your building. You're five minutes late, but at least you saved on fuel emissions and gas money!
You slide into your Dodge Charger and turn the ignition. The engine rumbles to a start before leveling off to a purr. You're feeling READY. You head to work. It takes you only five minutes.
